<DOC><DOCNO> AP881020-0129 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-20-88 1224EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Greece-Terrorism     10-20 0120</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Greece-Terrorism,0124</SECOND><HEAD>Police Conduct Anti-Terrorist Exercises In Athens</HEAD><DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Police cordoned off sections of thecapital Thursday to conduct anti-terrorist exercises, a governmentspokesman said.   The exercise tested the ability of a new anti-terrorist policeunit, said the spokesman, Sotiris Kostopoulos.   The government has stepped up its anti-terrorism capabilityafter Arab gunmen opened fire on a Greek cruise ship in July,killing nine people and injuring 98 others.   Police also are fighting two Greek organizations _ November 17,which claims a dozen political killings, and Revolutionary PopularStruggle, responsible for hundreds of bombings but no deaths.   In August, November 17 raided a police station, held five policeofficers at gunpoint and fled with arms and ammunition.</TEXT></DOC>